(http://www.nutch.org/), from the website, &quot;Nutch is a
nascent effort to implement an open-source web search
engine.&quot;

An evaluation by OSU mentioned &quot;Both Google and Nutch
did very well in a manual comparison of the most
frequent queries on the OSU website. Google did
slightly better overall.&quot;

http://www.nutch.org/twiki/Main/Evaluations/OSU_Queries.pdf

Nutch has a crawler and the search engine is based on
Lucene. I wonder if there is any initiative to
translate format between nutch and Heritrix, but I
think it makes sense to crawl a website just once.

